2026-03-01T10:02:50.3168920Z Note: a multi-user installation is possible. See https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/installation/installing-binary.html#multi-user-installation
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3179929Z [1;31mSwitching to the Multi-user Installer[0m
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3287393Z [32mWelcome to the Multi-User Nix Installation
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3298355Z [0m
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3298760Z This installation tool will set up your computer with the Nix package
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3299410Z manager. This will happen in a few stages:
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3299755Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3300049Z 1. Make sure your computer doesn't already have Nix. If it does, I
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3300840Z    will show you instructions on how to clean up your old install.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3301629Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3302123Z 2. Show you what I am going to install and where. Then I will ask
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3303045Z    if you are ready to continue.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3303324Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3303912Z 3. Create the system users [34m(uids [30001..30008])[0m and groups [34m(gid 30000)[0m
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3304854Z    that the Nix daemon uses to run builds. To create system users
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3305602Z    in a different range, exit and run this tool again with
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3306149Z    NIX_FIRST_BUILD_UID set.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3306401Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3306719Z 4. Perform the basic installation of the Nix files daemon.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3307128Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3307443Z 5. Configure your shell to import special Nix Profile files, so you
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3308377Z    can use Nix.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3308603Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3308756Z 6. Start the Nix daemon.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3309001Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3309533Z [32m[4;32mWould you like to see a more detailed list of what I will do?
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3310273Z [0mNo TTY, assuming you would say yes :)
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3314853Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3315085Z I will:
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3315478Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3315959Z  - make sure your computer doesn't already have Nix files
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3316600Z    (if it does, I will tell you how to clean them up.)
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3317231Z  - create local users (see the list above for the users I'll make)
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3317677Z  - create a local group (nixbld)
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3317922Z  - install Nix in /nix
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3318160Z  - create a configuration file in /etc/nix
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3318511Z  - set up the "default profile" by creating some Nix-related files in
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3318831Z    /root
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3331342Z  - back up /etc/bash.bashrc to /etc/bash.bashrc.backup-before-nix
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3332172Z  - update /etc/bash.bashrc to include some Nix configuration
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3345901Z  - load and start a service (at /etc/systemd/system/nix-daemon.service
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3347093Z    and /etc/systemd/system/nix-daemon.socket) for nix-daemon
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3347527Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3348162Z [32m[4;32mReady to continue?
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3348732Z [0mNo TTY, assuming you would say yes :)
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3371131Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3372051Z [34m---- let's talk about sudo -----------------------------------------------------
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3385023Z [0mThis script is going to call sudo a lot. Normally, it would show you
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3385861Z exactly what commands it is running and why. However, the script is
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3386484Z run in a headless fashion, like this:
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3386787Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3386995Z   $ curl -L https://nixos.org/nix/install | sh
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3387350Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3387630Z or maybe in a CI pipeline. Because of that, I'm going to skip the
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3388241Z verbose output in the interest of brevity.
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3388566Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3388738Z If you would like to
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3389107Z see the output, try like this:
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3389367Z 
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3389613Z   $ curl -L -o install-nix https://nixos.org/nix/install
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3390133Z   $ sh ./install-nix
2026-03-01T10:02:50.3390337Z 
